body_html: I'm assuming that this question on Stack Overflow is related. It does sound like something is corrupting your files as you download them (since gunzip isn't working). Can you try downloading the files using wget or curl and ensuring that they work this way?

body: I'm assuming that [this question on Stack Overflow](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/36055090/zlib-error-error-3-while-decompressing-invalid-distance-code) is related. It does sound like something is corrupting your files as you download them (since `gunzip` isn't working). Can you try downloading the files using `wget` or `curl` and ensuring that they work this way?
